{"id":"reported-tn-8","label":"Reported Speech (TN 8)","lockAfter":3,"list":[{"id":"fillup","label":"Fill in the blanks","type":"fillup","commonData":{"title":"Direct and Indirect speech sentences are given. Fill in the blanks with the right option."},"data":["Kaitlyn said, “I am very busy now.”\nKaitlyn *said(told, asked)* that she was very busy *then(now, today)* .\nHe said he was cooking dinner.\nHe *told(said, asked)* me he was cooking dinner.\nHe said, “I am fine.” \nHe said *he(I, she, we)* *was (am, is)* fine. ","She said, “My sister is learning Karate.”\nShe said *her (my, me)* sister *was (is, will be)* learning Karate. \nHe said, “I have won the match.” \nHe said he *had (has, have)* won the match. \nShe said, “The horse died in the night.” \nShe said that the horse *had died (died, have died)* in the night. ","The teacher said, “The earth goes round the sun.”\nThe teacher said *the earth (earth)* *goes(went)* round the sun.\nThe Prince said, “It gives me great pleasure to be here this evening.”  \nThe Prince said that it *gave(gives, give)* him great pleasure to be there *that (this, in this)* evening.\nHe said to me, “What are you doing?” \nHe *asked (told)* me what *I was (was I)* doing. ","“Where do you live?” asked the stranger.\nThe stranger *enquired (questioned, asked)* where I lived. \nHe said, “Will you attend the meeting?”\nHe *asked(told)* them *whether(will)* *they (her, him)* would attend the meeting. \nRama said to Arjun, “Go away.” \nRama *ordered (asked, requested)* Arjun to go away."]},{"type":"makeSentence","label":"Convert questions to Reported speech","id":"make-sentence","data":{"title":"Change the following into Indirect Speech. Make sentence by dragging the words.","extras":" ","text":"“What do you want?” he said to her. | he asked her what she wanted\nHe said, “How's your father?”  | he asked me how my father was\n“Are you coming home with me?” he asked. | he asked me whether I was coming home with him\nThe poor man exclaimed, “Will none of you help me?”  | the poor man asked everyone whether any of them would help him\n“Don't you know the way home?” asked I.  | I asked her whether she knew the way home "}},{"type":"makeSentence","label":"Make Reported speech","id":"make-sentence-2","commonData":{"title":"Change the following into Indirect Speech. Make sentence by dragging the words.","extras":" "},"data":["“Bring me a glass of milk,” said the sage to the villagers. | the sage asked the villagers to bring him a glass of milk\n“Sit down, boys,” said the teacher. | the teacher ordered the boys to sit down\n“Halt!” shouted the officer to his men. | the officer shouted his men to halt\n“Take off your hat,” the king said to the Hatter. | the king ordered the Hatter to take off his hat\nThe teacher said to him, “Do not read so fast.” | the teacher ordered him not to read so fast","He said to me, “Wait until I come.” | he told me to wait until he came\n“Hurry up,” he said to his servant, “Do not waste time.”  | he ordered his servant to hurry up and not to waste time\n“Run away, children,” said their mother. | the mother told her children to run away\nHe said, “Daughter, take my golden jug, and fetch me some water from the Well.” | he told his daughter to take his golden jug and fetch him some water from the well\n“Go down to the bazaar. Bring me some oil and a lump of ice.” ordered his master. | the master ordered him to go down to the bazaar and bring some oil and a lump of ice."," \"What are you reading, Pushpa?\" asked Punitha. | Punitha asked Pushpa what she was reading\n\"I am reading Robinson Crusoe, Pushpa told her. | Pushpa told her that she was reading Robinson Crusoe\n\"What is it all about?\" Punitha asked. | Punitha asked her what it was all about\n\"It is about a man wrecked on an island,\" Pushpa said. | Pushpa said that it was about a man wrecked on an island\n\"Who gave you the book, Pushpa?\" Punitha then asked. | Punitha then asked who had given her the book\n\"My uncle gave it to me at Christmas,' answered Pushpa. | Pushpa answered that her uncle had given it to her at Christmas\n\"May I borrow it?\" inquired Punitha. |  Punitha inquired if she could borrow it \n\"Of course I will lend it to you,\" replied Pushpa. | Pushpa replied that she would certainly lend it to her "]},{"type":"makeSentence","label":"Reported to Direct Speech","id":"make-sentence-3","commonData":{"title":"Change the following into direct speech. Make sentence by dragging the words.","extras":" "},"data":["Nevin asked his father when the next letter would come.  | Nevin said to his father ,\" when will the next letter come ?\"\n  I wrote that I would visit him the next day. | I wrote ,\" I will visit him tomorrow \".\n  I told them to be quiet. | I said to them ,\" Be quiet !\".\n  Lakshan asked me if I had anything to say. | Lakshan said to me ,\" Do you have anything to say ?\"\nAn old mouse asked who would bell the cat. | an old mouse said ,\" Who will bell the cat ?\"","Mervin said that he wanted to be a soldier. | Mervin said ,\" I want to be a soldier .\"\nEbin asked me what I wanted. | Ebin said to me ,\" What do you want ?\"\nBhagya said that she had seen that picture. | Bhagya said ,\" I have seen that picture .\"\nThe stranger asked Nasrin where she lived. | The stranger said to Nasrin ,\" where do you live ?\"\nI asked Mary if she would lend me a pencil. | I said to Mary ,\" Will you lend me a pencil ?\""]}]}